article.headline: Wyoming 59, Air Force 33
article.story:
LARAMIE, Wyo. (AP) -- Hanna Zavecz had 14 points, five steals and
two blocked shots Saturday afternoon to lead Wyoming in a 59-33
rout of Air Force.

Air Force (12-10, 3-8 Mountain West) struggled on offense early,
committing three turnovers and going 0-5 from the field in the
first four minutes as Wyoming (16-6, 6-5) opened up an 8-0 lead.

Another 8-0 run, highlighted by 3-pointers from Jodi Bolerjack
and Dominique Sisk, put the Cowgirls up 16-6 with 10:44 left in the
first half.

Michelle Taylor made all six of her free throw attempts during a
15-4 run that extended Wyoming's lead to 33-14 at halftime. Taylor
finished the game with 12 points.

The Cowgirls used a 15-2 run to extend their lead to 57-27 with
5:07 remaining.

Pamela Findlay scored 13 points and grabbed seven rebounds to
lead Air Force, which shot just 29 percent from the field and had
22 turnovers.
